  <title>SRM Performance Logging</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>EMULATR_RETIRE_TRACE_DIR</keyword>
    <keyword>Performance Validator</keyword>
    <keyword>PipelineDriver</keyword>
    <keyword>profile file</keyword>
    <keyword>RetireProfiler</keyword>
    <keyword>retire-PC histogram</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header><para styleclass="Heading1">SRM Performance Logging</para></header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Performance-run output depends on which "performance run" you mean.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">EmulatR's own profiler</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The <text styleclass="Code Example">RetireProfiler</text> is an always-on retire-PC histogram in the <text styleclass="Code Example">PipelineDriver</text>. It writes <text styleclass="Code Example">profile_YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS_&lt;tag&gt;.txt</text> to the same resolved trace directory as the other sinks -- <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_RETIRE_TRACE_DIR</text> (the build-tree default otherwise). It moves automatically when that directory is overridden.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">External profiling tools</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">A Software Verify Performance Validator (PV) run is not written by EmulatR -- that is an external tool profiling <text styleclass="Code Example">Emulatr.exe</text>. Its session and results go wherever PV saves them (its <text styleclass="Code Example">-saveSession</text> path, or PV's default session folder under your Documents). Nothing in the codebase controls that; it is a PV-side setting.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See Also.</text></para>
